Who are we?

At Equinix, we make the internet work faster, better, and more reliably. We hire hardworking people who thrive on solving hard problems and give them opportunities to hone new skills, try new approaches, and grow in new directions. Our culture is at the heart of our success and it뭩 our authentic, humble, gritty people who craft The Magic of Equinix. They share a real passion for winning and put the customer at the center of everything they do.

If you are looking to join a company that can offer long term career opportunities on a global scale backed by a positive, and high energy culture, then Equinix is the place for you!

Job Summary:

Responsible for network design and planning, capacity management, vendor evaluation, activation and deactivation of customer services, troubleshooting and fault resolution of reported and detected faults. Performs effective maintenance to the equipment to prevent faults from occurring; procurement and installation of equipment for expansion and new services.

Responsibilities

Deployment
 Learns and understands the network devices being deployed
 Participates in Lunch &amp; Learn session to train the team
 Participates in global tech drills and learns hands-on devices to train

Product Development Lifecycle Engagements
 Test Phase: Acts as a function SME and participates in UATs
 Trains the teams once UAT is complete

Service Delivery
 Performs network service fulfillment for quote to cash transactional tickets for all network and data center products (Interconnections, DCIM etc.)
 Generates metrics based on Service Delivery metrics on a periodic basis

Innovations
 Participates in events like Sparkathon to trigger innovation in process
 Uses the shared lab setups to practices the exercises published by the NetOps Technical Leadership team
 Participates in Simian Army based Tech drills focused on driving service excellence targeting a (break, learn, fix, resume) exercises on lab setups
